cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the access reservation protocol in LTE networks for Machine-Type Communications. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it proposes a low-complexity model to evaluate the outage probability. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the limitations of the LTE access reservation protocol and proposes a model to overcome them. It may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as MTC devices may transmit multimedia data, and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as security is an important aspect of MTC.
